descript.abstract:
The HUC-11 coverage for the Chespaeake Bay watershed states--referred to here as the Mid-Atlantic states--level is an aggregate of the individual state coverages clipped to the Cheaspeake Bay Basin boundaries. These states are Delaware, Maryland, New York, Pennsylvania, Virginia, West Virginia, and Washington, D.C. This aggregate HUC-11 data set has been modified by the Chesapeake Bay Program GIS Team to ensure edge matching and closed watersheds along state boundaries. In addition, the aggregate HUC-11 coverage includes watershed boundaries for the state of DE (these watershed boundaries were provided by DE, but these is not an official DE HUC-11 coverage), and a small portion of the Chesapeake Bay Basin in NY State that does not yet have officially designated HUC-11 boundaries has been 'filled-in' with watershed boundaries by delineating and digitizing them from 1:24,000 scaled USGS topographic maps of the area by the Chesapeake Bay Program GIS Team. There are a total of 506 HUC-11/watersheds for the Chesapeake Bay Basin in this aggregate data set.
This is the same coverage as huc11_hr except that a previously missing watershed on the edge of the basin west of Cortland, NY has been added.
descript.purpose: Originally compiled for Chesapeake Bay Program mapping and analysis.
descript.supplinf: HUC-11 boundaries are compiled by each state. The export files of HUC-11 at the state level were provided by each respective state and are unmodified. HUC-11 boundaries for Delaware are not yet available. Also, a small portion of the Chesapeake Basin in NY State has not yet been completed.
